// gate_stack_lower — Right Utility Switchback (intro-v1 Task 05).
//
// Beat: route-choice junction. Drain Market on the left, official
// gate signage and a portal mechanic in the middle, a sky tease at
// the top, a private side entrance from the Alice/Bob route at the
// bottom (forward-declared), and the combat calibration lab on the
// right. The room shows multiple access models side by side so the
// player understands official/private/neutral/chaotic before any
// dialogue explains them.
//
// Identifier kept as `gate_stack_lower` so existing LoadingZone
// targets in drain_alley and central_hub_complex do not need
// rewriting. Comments / debug labels carry the utility-switchback
// reinterpretation. worldX corrected from the stale spec value
// 108000 to the live value 4928.
//
// Transitions:
// - Left-edge EdgeExit `gate_stack_from_drain` ← drain_alley
// - Right-edge EdgeExit `gate_to_combat_lab` → combat_calibration_lab
//   (Task 05 stub; Task 06 fills out the lab interior.)
// - Mid-room Door `pirate_sky_up` → pirate_sky_arena (existing).
// - Mid-room Door `intro_portal_zone` → central_hub_complex
//   (existing, gated by `intro_portal_switch` via `GatedZoneRegistry`).
// - Forward-declared: a `gate_from_alice_private` connection from
//   alice_relay's `alice_private_return_lock` once Task 08 wires
//   `bob_field_survey_received` into the gating registry. For now a
//   LockWall + label holds the slot.

